# GitLab → Settings → CI/CD → Variables (group or project)
#
# --- Deploy (Type = Variable) ---
# PROD_SERVER_IP
# PROD_SSH_USER             e.g. ubuntu
# PROD_REPO_DIR             optional; default /home/ubuntu/prod/vidhigya
# PROD_SSH_PRIVATE_KEY      base64-encoded private key, single line (common parent name)
#   Optional alias: PROD_SSH_PRIVATE_KEY_B64 (used if PROD_SSH_PRIVATE_KEY is empty)
#
# Group variables missing in job? Typical causes:
#   - Variable is Protected but the pipeline runs on an unprotected branch → protect `prod`.
#   - Environment scope is "production" but job had no environment → deploy job sets environment: production.
#   - Project defines same key with empty value → overrides parent; delete or fix at project level.
#
# --- App env (Type = File) ---
# WEB_ENV_FILE              → apps/web/.env
# BACKEND_ENV_FILE          → apps/backend/.env
# AI_ENV_FILE               → apps/ai-service/.env
